.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "August 2024" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B simple_shell
is a basic UNIX command line interpreter. It provides a prompt for the user to enter commands and executes them.

It supports the following features:
.TP
.B Interactive Mode
Displays a prompt and waits for the user to enter a command. After executing the command, it displays the prompt again.
.TP
.B Non-Interactive Mode
Reads commands from standard input (e.g., a pipe) and executes them.

.SH COMMANDS
The shell handles commands in the following way:
.TP
.B ls
Lists directory contents.
.TP
.B /bin/ls
Executes the /bin/ls command directly.

.SH BUILT-INS
The following built-in commands are supported:
.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell.
.TP
.B env
Prints the current environment variables.

.SH OPTIONS
This shell does not support any additional options or arguments. Commands must be entered directly without arguments.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell exits with status code 0 if the command was successful, and a non-zero value if an error occurred.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B $ ./simple_shell
Displays the shell prompt.
.TP
.B $ /bin/ls
Lists the files in the current directory.
.TP
.B $ exit
Exits the shell.

